@node Autor "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Note from author:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    Hola Amigos!!!!

    A new update of AmiMSX, new features:

    - MSX2 Overscan support. (256x224 pixels)  (Sex Bomb Bunny)
    - Screen 2 and 4 ONE tile bank support.  (Ark-A-Noah)
    - Screen 8 Sprites are now emulated with your real colours.
    - Syncronized CPU emulation. (Real / Fast / Turbo modes)
    - 100% Compatible with all Motorola Procesors. (020/030/040/060)
    - Full support of Line Interrupts.


    There are two games included with AmiMSX to test these two features:

    Sex Bomb Bunny:  A sexy game in Screen 8 with overscan support.

    Ark-A-Noah:  A game in Screen 4 with overscan support and uses
ONE bank tiles instead of 4.

    These two games ONLY works 100% with AmiMSX, I not found any other
MSX emulator capable of emulate them correctly!!!

    These games are © Matra Corporation 'www.matranet.net' A new group
making great games for MSX.  Take a look to your web!!!!

    Greetings!

    Juan

@endnode


@node Introduccio "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Introduction:
@{fg text}    -------------

    This program emulates a 8-bit MSX2 computer.

    Quality of emulation depends on the Amiga system that is used.

    This program does not multitask and freezes the Operating System to
obtain a good quality emulation, programming directly the Amiga's custom
chips.


@{fg highlight}    DISCLAIMER:
@{fg text}    -----------
    THE AUTHOR DOESN'T GUARANTEE THAT THIS PROGRAM EMULATES A FULL MSX2,
AND ACCEPTS NO RESPONSIBILITY FOR LOSS OF DATA DERIVED FROM THE USE OF
THIS SOFTWARE...

@endnode


@node Requeriments "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Minimal Requirements:
@{fg text}    --------------------------

    - AMIGA computer with AGA chipset
    - MC68020+
    - DEVS:mfm.device           (For DiskDrives emulation)
    - DEVS:statram.device       (For RAMSX: drive emulation)
    - LIBS:stc020.library v3.0+
    - LIBS:asl.library
    - 3MB of memory (1Mb Chip)
    - PAL, NTSC or compatible monitor.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Extra requirements for real MSX2 emulation:
@{fg text}    ------------------------------------------------

    - MC68020 at 28Mz or faster Processor
    - 2Mb of 32-bit Fast memory

@endnode


