@node MenuPro "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Project Menu:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> About:
@{fg text}    ----------

    Information about the author and addresses.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Menu Screen:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Set menu screen in PAL or NTSC.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Screen:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Save the emulated screen like a IFF-ILBM file.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Cheat mode:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    For finding/setting cheat pokes in the MSX2 emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Prefs:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    Save preferences and MSX2 clock battery in S:MSX2emulator.prefs

@{fg highlight}    <*> Quit:
@{fg text}    ---------

    To quit the emulator.

@endnode

@node MenuOpt "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Options menu:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Joystick 2 ON:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    To activate emulation of the second MSX Joystick.  (It must be
connected in the Amiga's mouse connector.)

    Note:  This menu needs to be disabled for MSX mouse emulation.

    Caution:  If this menu is activated and your Amiga mouse is connected
some games will not work well.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Swap JoyPorts:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    Change JoyPorts A and B of MSX.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Multi-key ON:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    There is a bug in the Amiga 1200 keyboard, and some keys can't be
pressed together.  To solve this, you can activate this menu and then
press all keys you want separately.  MSX rom will think that you are
pressing all keys at the same time until you disable this menu.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Left and Right Shift as Space:
@{fg text}    ----------------------------------

    Will emulate Left or Right Shift keys as Space.  (To solve the A1200
Space and Down key bug.)


@{fg highlight}    <*> DEL for Pause:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    Amiga's DEL key will pause the emulation if this menu is enabled.
    To exit pause press DEL key again.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Ask for Power ON:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    If this menu is enabled the emulation will ask for a confirmation
when you click on Power ON.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Japanese ID:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Emulates a MSX ROM bios Japanese.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Kanji ROM:
@{fg text}    --------------

    Emulates MSX Kanji ROM.


@{fg highlight}    <*> MSX Virtual Disk:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    - MVD: Write Protected:  Disk in MVD:  will be write-protected.

    - Warn on save to protected MVD:  Emulation is stopped when you atten
to save in a Write-Pretected MVD.

    - Warn when MVD:  buffer is changed:  AmiMSX warn if MVD has been
changed when you press HELP key.  This is to remenber save MVD in your
harddisk.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Screen Mode on Exit:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

    Force to set screen mode to PAL, NTSC, or no change.

@endnode

@node MenuMVD "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    MSX Virtual Drive menu:
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    AmiMSX Emulator supports a MSX Virtual Drive in Amiga's RAM.

    You can have MSX disks of 360Kb (1DD) or 720Kb (2DD) crunched as
Amiga files on your hard Disk, CD-ROM, etc...

    MVD files can be crunched with Stone Cracker or File Imploder
(supported in emulator).

    Note:  MVD files are MSX Disk Images.  (#?.dsk)

@{fg highlight}    <*> Load/Save Disk File:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

    To Load/Save MVD files.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Load/Save MSX Disk:
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    To Load/Save from/to MSX Disk.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Install MSX Boot:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    To install MSX boot on MSX Disks.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Implode MVD:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Will crunch the resident MVD with File Imploder.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Format MVD as 2DD or 1DD:
@{fg text}    -----------------------------

    Create a buffer (MVD:) of a 1DD/2DD MSX disk.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Clear Buffer:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    Clear MVD: buffer  (as an Eject disk of MVD: drive)

@endnode

@node MenuCar "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Cartridges:
@{fg text}    -----------

    This is for emulate MSX Cartridges of ANY size.

    Slot 3 is for obtaining cartridge files but it is a bit complicated
to explain!!!

@{fg highlight}    Slot 1 & 2:
@{fg text}    -----------

    - Insert Cartridge: For reading a cartridge file.

    - Eject Cartridge:  For ejecting the cartridge file that is resident.

    - Save Mapper ID:  Saves Mapper type for current Cartridge.  When you
insert this cartridge again, your mapper will be set correctly.


@{fg highlight}    Mapper:
@{fg text}    -------

    MSX cartridges bigger than 32Kb uses a custom mapper to work.

    There are six types of mappers emulated in AmiMSX.  You need find the
correct mapper for a Cartridge testing every one.


@{fg highlight}    Slot 3:
@{fg text}    -------

    This option is for 'programers'

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save Pages:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    - Page 1:  Save Page 1 of Slot 3 (&H4000-&H7FFF)

    - Page 2:  Save Page 2 of Slot 3 (&H8000-&HBFFF)

    - Page 1 & 2:  Save Pages 1 and 2 of Slot 3 (&H4000-&HBFFF)

@endnode

@node FinestraPrin "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Disk Drives:
@{fg text}    ------------

    With these gadgets you select which Amiga-diskdrives will be used to
emulate MSX drives A:  and B: . If both A:  and B:  drives are OFF, MSX
Disk Basic ROM will not be emulated.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  MSX Drive A & B:
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    - DFx:   Emulation of MSX drives via  Amiga drives.

    - MVD:   Emulation of @{"MSX Virtual Drive" link MenuMVD} (MVD:)

    - RAMSX: Emulation of Amigas's RAD: as a MSX disk. (Look at @{"RAMSX:" link RAMSX})

    - OFF:   Emulation of NO drive connected.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  MSX Disk ROM:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    - DOS:   Emulation of Disk ROM v1.0  (Recommended for Games)

    - DOS2:  Emulation of Disk ROM v2.0  (Recommended for Tools)

    - None:  Emulation of NO Disk ROM.

@{fg highlight}    Slots Options:
@{fg text}    --------------

@{fg highlight}    <*>  ROM:
@{fg text}    ---------

    - MSX:  Emulation of MSX ROM.

    - MSX2: Emulation of MSX2 ROM.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  RAM:
@{fg text}    ---------

    - Emulation of 128 to 4096Kb RAM.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Sound:
@{fg text}    -----------

    - PSG:  Emulation of PSG.

    - SCC:  Emulation of Konami's SCC.

    - SCC+: Emulation of Konami's SCC+.


@{fg highlight}    Video Options:
@{fg text}    --------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Frequence:
@{fg text}    --------------

    -  Selects display mode:

         * [From VDP] MSX will select NTSC or PAL when required.
         * [No Change] MSX won't be able to change display mode.
         * [PAL] (50 Hz) The emulator will always run in PAL mode.
         * [NTSC] (60 Hz) The emulator will always run in NTSC mode.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Refresh:
@{fg text}    ------------

    MSX screen is updated every 'refresh' frames.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Sprites:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    MSX2 Sprites refresh:

    - OFF: No sprite emulation.

    - 1fr: Refresh at 1 frame. (100%)

    - 2fr: Refresh at 2 frames.  (50%)

    - 3fr: Refresh at 3 frames.  (36%)


@{fg highlight}    Rest of the Gadgets:
@{fg text}    ----------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> MVD:
@{fg text}    --------

    For reading a MSX Virtual Disk in MVD:

@{fg highlight}    <*> Emulation Speed:
@{fg text}    --------------------

 - [Real MSX]  MSX runs always at 3.5Mhz

 - [Fast CPU]  MSX CPU run as fast possible.

 - [Turbo Mode] MSX run at 3.5Mhz but without wait to 'Amiga Real Frame'


@{fg highlight}    <*> Slot 1 and 2:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    For reading a cartridge file in any Slot.

@{fg highlight}    Reset:
@{fg text}    ------

    Makes a MSX reset. (Like key RESET of a MSX keyboard)

@{fg highlight}    <*> Power ON:
@{fg text}    -------------

    For starting MSX2 emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Continue:
@{fg text}    -------------

    To continue the emulation after you have pressed the HELP key.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Exit:
@{fg text}    ---------

    To quit the emulator.

@endnode

@node FinestraIMP "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Imploder window:
@{fg text}    ----------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Implode:
@{fg text}    ------------

    To crunch a resident MSX Virtual Disk in MVD:

@{fg highlight}    <*> Efficiency:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    Compression efficiency.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Abort:
@{fg text}    ----------

    Not implemented!

@{fg highlight}    <*> Save:
@{fg text}    ---------

    To save crunched MVD.

@{fg highlight}    <*> Cancel:
@{fg text}    -----------

    To exit to main menu.

@endnode

@node FinestraPoke "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Cheat window:
@{fg text}    -------------

@{fg highlight}    <*> Find Poke:
@{fg text}    --------------

    This is for finding a cheat address.

    First set the actual nr. of lives for which to Search.
    Go back to the emulation and loose one life.
    Go to this window and set the actual nr. of lives in Compare With.
    Now, in Address Found, you can find a possible cheat address!

@{fg highlight}    <*> Poke:
@{fg text}    ---------

    When you click Do poke, a poke is done in MSX memory.

                           ( Poke Address,Value )

    Some cheat poke Addresses:
    --------------------------
GORBY'S PIPELINE:       LEVEL=$C80C (INS 1-8) : PIPES=$C80D (DEL ONCE)
NYANACLE:               LIVES=$D215  TIME=$D214
PUYO PUYO:              BLOCKS=$C976  SCORE=$C978
DRAGONSLAYER 6:         HP PLAYER 1,2,4=$2344,$2804,$2384,$23C4
BREAKER:                BALLS=$953D
PEACH UP (WIP WAP):     LIVES=$D28C
PEACH UP (HAMMERTJE)    $CE03,$CE02
PEACH UP (PEACH SLOT):  GOLD=$6070
PEACH UP (HYPERBLOCK):  BALLS=$5D16
PEACH UP (SHOOTER):     BOMBS&LIVES=$D209,$D208
HYDEFOS:                ENERGIE&LIVES&SCORE=$C11C,$D404,$D406
NINJA DEXTER:           MAGIC=$D46F
PACMANIA:               LIVES=$D033
YS 1:                   GOLD&EXP&HP=$CFC7,$CFC9,$CFC3
YS 2:                   GOLD&EXP&MP=$0196,$0102,$0104
YS 3:                   HP&EXP&RING=$7FA7,$7FA0,$7EA0
PRINCESS:               LIVES=$CE06
FAMICLE PARODIC:        LIVES=$E003
FAMICLE PARODIC II:     LIVES=$C008
LAST TESTAMENT:         GRENADES=$59DE
USAS:                   COINS=$C259
MARAYA:                 GOLD&FIRE,LIVES,LIFE,KEYS,BOMBS=$CCD4,$CD74,$CCBC,$CCD3,$CD75,$CD76
TWINKLE STAR GAMES:     LIVES=$4052
NO FUSS:                LIVES=$7FFE
GREATEST DRIVER:        QUALIFY LAPS (P1)=$A256
GREATEST DRIVER:        QUALIFY LAPS (P2)=$A28B
ALESTE SPECIAL:         LIVES=$D080  LEVEL=$D00B
QUINPL:                 LIVES=$BC11
CHUCKA TAISEN:          LIVES=$A685
ARTIC EXCITMENT:        LIVES=$FB35
PLAYBALL 3:             SCORE,TEGENSTANDER=$D480,$D47F
SUPER COOKS:            LIVES=$CB39

@endnode

@node RAMSX "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    RAMSX: drive
@{fg text}    ------------

    RAMSX:  is a drive for emulating a MSX disk using Amiga's RAD:.

    Before using, you need to mount it.  (Like PCx:)

    Now you can save files from WorkBench to RAMSX:  and read these files in
the emulator.

    Note:  If you save files from the emulator, you need to do:

    DiskChange RAMSX:

    Now Amiga can read RAMSX:  as well.

    Note:  RAMSX:  uses StaticRAM.devive and not ramdrive!!!

@endnode


