@node Z80A "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Z-80A  (Processor):   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    ------------------------

    All works correctly except this:

    - Flags N and H are not emulated
    - Flag P is only emulated at instructions OR, AND, XOR
    - R register not emulated well

@endnode


@node Dibuixos "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    VDP  (Graphics chip):   Emulated at 85%.
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    All works correctly except this:

    * Sprites:
        - Expanded Sprites
        - Sprites Collisions

    * MSX-Video:
        - XOR mode emulated as NOT
        - Line logical operators
        - Color search

@endnode

@node Soroll "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  PSG  (Sound Chip):   Emulated at 99%.   
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    It works correctly.


@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC  (Sound Custom Chip):   Emulated at 98%.   
@{fg text}    ------------------------------

    Amiga cannot emulate it correctly:

    - The SCC chip has 5 channels and Amiga only 4, when it uses 5
channels, channel 5 will not be emulated.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC+  (Sound Custom Chip+):   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    --------------------------------

    Emulation is equal to SCC.

@endnode

@node Jocs "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Joystick ports:
@{fg text}    --------------------

    Two firebuttons in MSX are supported.  Left and Right Amiga keys work
like joystick second firebutton.

    A Joypad can be used.

    Amiga firebutton 1 = MSX firebutton 1
    Amiga firebutton 2 & 3 = MSX firebutton 2    

    Amiga A port = MSX B port
    Amiga B port = MSX A port


@{fg highlight}    <*> Mouse:
@{fg text}    ----------

    MSX mouse is emulated in port A of MSX when Joystick 2 menu is
disabled.

    Amiga mouse needs to be connected in port A of Amiga.

@endnode

@node Teclat "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Keyboard:   Emulated at 99%. 
@{fg text}    --------------

    MSX keyboard is the same as Amiga's except for the following keys:
    (English keymap only)

                          AMIGA       MSX
                         -------     -----
                            F6       SELECT
                            F7       STOP
                            F8       HOME/CLS
                            F9       INS
                           F10       DEL
                      Left ALT       GRAPH
                     Right ALT       CODE

                            ` ~      ń Ń  (In MSX2 ROM only)
                            DEL      MSX DEL or MSX Pause (optional)
                            [ {      Caps Lock.
                            < >      Caps Lock.
                            ç Ç      Dead key. (accents)
                            ] }      Dead key. (accents)

                     Left Amiga      JoyStick 1 - 2nd firebutton
                    Right Amiga      JoyStick 2 - 2nd firebutton

             CTRL+Left ALT+DEL       MSX Reset
             CTRL+Left ALT+HELP      MSX Hard Reset

                           HELP      Go to Workbench's menu. (Exit)


    Note:  Ń or ń is a Spanish letter.

@endnode

@node Disc "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Disk drive:   Emulated at 99%.
@{fg text}    ----------------

    For a good emulation of MSX drives you need to mount PCx:  of the
drive that you are using.

    Note:  If PCx:  is not mounted 1DD MSX disks will fail!

    Make sure your disks have got a MSX boot to avoid a hang up when the
MSX is booting from a disk drive.  You can install it, using "MSX Boot"
gadget.
    DO NOT INSTALL ALL DISKS you get, because some MSX disks had their
own boot to run the game.  Install only disks that you've formatted in a
PC or using PCx:  drives.

    To emulate MSX disk drives I have had to "kill" the interrupt that
warns the Amiga that a disk has been changed, so when you exit the
emulator the diskdrive will not recognise Amiga disks.  I am sorry.

    But you can do this to recover Amiga drives:

    ASSIGN DFx:  dismount
    MOUNT DFx:

    You need to do a mount-list with DFx:  datas.

@endnode

@node Altres "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Memory:
@{fg text}    ------------
    You can emulate from 128 to 4096Kb RAM amd 128Kb VRAM.

    Sub-Slots (&HFFFF) are not supported, so there are NO COMPATIBILITY
PROBLEMS with Sony or Philips memory models!

    If you get an "out of memory" error, try to disable drive B:
emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Clock Battery:
@{fg text}    -------------------
    
    Correctly emulated except the time!


@{fg highlight}    <*>  Printer port:
@{fg text}    ------------------

    Emulation by Sergi Martinez.

    It work 100%

@endnode


@node incompatibilitat "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Errors and incompatibility:
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

    This version is very reliable, if a game does not work it can be a
general MSX incompatibility problem.  (Not all MSX games worked on all
MSX configurations.  Like with some Amiga software today.  (Ed.))

    If you run into an incompatibility problem try to do the following:

    - Set Disk-Drive B: to OFF.
    - Set RAM: to 256Kb.
    - Set DOS instead DOS2.

@endnode


@node Tecnics "AmiMSX Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Technical data:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    This program was developed 100% in assembly language on an AMIGA
1200+Blizzard 1220 (MC68020 at 28Mz and 4Mb of 32-bit Fast RAM).

    I have currently a Blizzard 1260!!!!  (Thanks Latok/Balance)

    To get the highest possible emulation speed this program disables
multitasking and programs the Amiga's custom chips directly.

    The MSX2 used for checking is a Philips NMS-8280 MSX2 computer.

    All sources of this emulator are designed and programmed by the me.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Slots Configuration:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

                       Slot 0  Slot 1  Slot 2  Slot 3
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 0 | Bios  |       | Sub   |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 1 | Basic |       | Disk  |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 2 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 3 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|


@{fg highlight}    <*> Emulation speed:  (±5%)
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

           Setup             Time     Z-80A       %      Accelerator
   ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
   MSX2  Philips NMS-8280     864     3.5Mz     100%
   ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
   Amiga 1200/20  28Mz.       600     5.0Mz     144%    Blizzard 1220
   Amiga 1200/30  50Mz.       183     8.3Mz     236%    Blizzard 1230-IV
   Amiga 1200/60  50Mz.       136    22.2Mz     635%    Blizzard 1260
   ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------

Note: Test included in 'MVD files/Speed Test.MVD'

@endnode


